{
  "slug": "agate-stone-marbling",
  "title": "Agate stone marbling",
  "subtitle": "Creating the banded, irregular stone-agate pattern from a concentric-drop base",
  "excerpt": "The stone-agate marble imitates the banded translucency of polished agate. It begins with a bouquet base of nested colour drops, modified by dragging one colour into concentric rings with a pin or stylus to suggest the curved banding of the stone. The pattern is one of the oldest named marble types in Western bookbinding.",
